What to check before submitting a bug report

Though bug reports are always appreciated it is best to check whether your bug is due to the program or your local configuration. It is quite hard to make these differences apart. Hopefully information on this page will help you determine whether or not to submit the report.
You should ask yourself a few questions to know where the problem lies:

If you are using windows vista this is one of the biggest problems MiniCoder or any other video encoding program has. Though this problem is largely solved by giving administrative rights to the program it is best to disable it and try again.
Do I have a codec pack installed?
Make sure you have a complete codec pack installed like K-Lite or CCCP. You can download one of them here:
Have I checked the Wiki for my problem?
Due to the long Beta phase of MiniCoder a lot of problems have occurred and have been solved already. These are usually configuration problems or system inconsistencies. You can find the wiki at
If all of these questions are answered with “Yes” then you should send in your bug report. Hopefully your problems will be solved in the next release.
Feel free to type any additional information here.
